# Testing Conventions — packages/ui

- Test the composed components (`EmptyState`, `LoadingState`, `ErrorState`,
  `StatBadge`, `OfflineBanner`, `PageHeader`) — these have real conditional
  rendering logic worth covering.
- Don't write tests for the raw shadcn/radix primitive wrappers
  (`button.tsx`, `card.tsx`, ...) beyond a smoke test if any — Radix already
  owns that behavior's correctness; re-testing it here is low-value.
- Query by role/label/text, not by class name or `data-testid`.
